                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "PURPOSE"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 10,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The purpose of this Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) is to:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 11,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Outline the principles of access planning"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 12,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Document the process for managing patients with access planning"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 13,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Provide a baseline for future process improvements"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 14,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Assist in developing baseline for the development of training material"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 15,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "OVERVIEW"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 16,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Access planning supports a structured and process driven approach to managing waiting lists. The relationship between an access plan and appointment is 1:1. A single access plan cannot support a series of bookings. An access plan entry (APE) is open until the appointment that is booked against it is departed. Once the appointment has taken place the related access plan entry is closed. Access plans and appointment outcoming must be carried out in the correct sequence or a number of data quality errors can occur."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Role \u2013 Administrative Procedure \u2013 Manage offer"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Additional guidance"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "This SOP does not describe the prioritisation of patients that require booking or how to use the PTL. The trigger for booking a patient from an access plan could be:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "At the request of service"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Patient contact (call, email, in person)"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Clinic capacity located (possibly from a short notice cancellation)"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "If \u2018manage offer' is carried out from the access plan entry the search for appointments is based on the rules in the patient access plan and the overarching access plan profile. This means in some cases user will be aware of an available clinic slot but be unable to locate it via the \u2018check availability'. Equally if a patient APE cannot be found from the clinic pegboard the access plan profile should be checked to ensure compatibility."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Where a slot has been found from a clinic pegboard view:"
            }
